This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a novel branch-and-bound algorithm, which is a common technique used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and optimization (cs.DM) problems. The paper also conducts experiments on real-world graphs, which suggests that it may belong to the cs.CC (Computational Complexity) sub-category.
